    <summary>Specifies whether a <see cref="T:System.Workflow.Activities.Rules.Rule" /> can be reevaluated.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 This enumeration is used to limit the number of times that a <xref:System.Workflow.Activities.Rules.Rule> runs, primarily to prevent infinite loops. The default value for this field is `Always`. This means that the number of times the <xref:System.Workflow.Activities.Rules.Rule> is run is not limited, and the <xref:System.Workflow.Activities.Rules.Rule> can be run as many times as determined by the chaining cycles in the <xref:System.Workflow.Activities.Rules.RuleSet> evaluation.  
  
 ]]></format>
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
